Sequence matrices were aligned by Cluster W and edited manually using MEGA 11 (
Tamura et al. 2021
). Genetic distances were also calculated in MEGA 11 by Kimura-2-parameter models (K2P) ( Kimura 1980 ), where 1000 replications for Bootstrap and gaps or missing data complete deletion were selected. Construction of the phylogenetic tree was performed by Maximum Likelihood (ML) analyses using IQ-TREE as implemented in the web online server (
Trifinopoulos et al. 2016
), with branch support values evaluated based on 1000 replicates for SH-aLRT and ultrafast bootstrap. Moreover, some pierid species are selected for molecular comparison with their Cytb genes obtained from NCBI GenBank ( Table 1 ).

